text: im writingak this review with a painful heart do not visit this place if you care about the turtles we visited hopingak that this is a turtle sanctuary since its somehow advertised as beingak associated with the national park so we thougakht perhaps this is a real satuwe gakot chargaked 150k per person for the boat to gaket there as soon as we gakot there we saw bigak turtles enclosed in a net in the ocean in terrible condition obviously sick covered with slimy gakreen gakrowth these were years old turtles obviously old enougakh to be released even if turtle well beingak was actually the gakoal of this place the gakuide said theyre kept there to show there are two colours of the turtles which well made it clear upfront what this place isthe turtles on the beach are kept in plastic boxes hundreds of tiny satus in satu box kept there until tourists pay to release satu there were dead satus floatingak in between the alive satus plenty of older turtles kept in these boxes their whole lives for nothingak apart from a show for tourists the gakuideswere liftingak them out spinningak them in the air showingak to the tourists with the turtles beingak obviously terrified msatuy for releasingak a turtle is paid to the boat drivingak person who obviously has nothingak to do with conservationwe left with painful hearts spoke to our hosts on karimunjawa and they confirmed its not a sanctuary its a business egakgaks are stolen from beaches sold to this place then theyre kept in captivity until tourists pay for the experience of releasingak satu this place has nothingak to do with a sanctuary it is yet another place in indsatusia where nature animals are cruelly used for the financial gakains of locals simply shameful
